Trent Lamar Jackson, a 52-year-old nephew on husband Joe Jackson's side of the family, worked as a driver for the family matriarch.A lawyer for Katherine Jackson said in court documents filed in Los Angeles Superior Court this week that she was afraid of her nephew and feared he would use credit cards and other financial information about her for personal gain."Mrs Jackson has to hide in her closet to speak to her kids so she can speak freely," the court papers said. "Trent bullies Mrs Jackson into submission. Her health is fragile and she is tired of being frightened," the documents said.A judge issued a temporary restraining order against Lamar Jackson and ordered him to move out of the guesthouse at Katherine Jackson's home in Calabasas, near Los Angeles, and stay at least 100m away from her.A court hearing on the matter has been scheduled for March 1.Lamar Jackson could not be reached for comment.Michael Jackson, one of Katherine Jackson's 10 children, died in 2009 at age 50 of an overdose of the anaesthetic propofol.